    <item>
      <title>OpenAI Losing Money on ChatGPT Pro: Sam Altman’s Pricing Drama</title>
      <link>https://raf-97414.github.io/en/posts/oops-moment/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 06 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://raf-97414.github.io/en/posts/oops-moment/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;💬 &lt;strong&gt;Sam Altman&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;ldquo;Let’s charge $200/month for ChatGPT Pro! Easy money!&amp;rdquo; 🤑&lt;br&gt;&#xA;👨‍💻 &lt;strong&gt;Users&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;ldquo;Oh, really? Watch this.&amp;rdquo; (Proceeds to use it like an all-you-can-eat AI buffet.) 🍔🤖&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Turns out, &lt;strong&gt;running ChatGPT costs more than a yacht habit&lt;/strong&gt;. At one point, it was &lt;strong&gt;$700K/day&lt;/strong&gt; to keep the AI thinking. 💸&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;OpenAI has now entered &lt;em&gt;panic mode&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 1:&lt;/strong&gt; Admit they need &amp;ldquo;way more money than imagined.&amp;rdquo; 😬&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 2:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ldquo;Should we raise prices?&amp;rdquo; 💰💭&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Despite burning cash like a flamethrower 🔥, they’re dreaming big: &lt;strong&gt;$100 billion revenue by 2029&lt;/strong&gt;. (Yes, the same sales as Nestlé. AI KitKats, anyone?) 🍫🤖&lt;/p&gt;</description>
